name: Biden news
summary: These articles cover various perspectives on Joe Biden's performance in the recent presidential debate. While some, such as the CBS News poll and an NBC News article, highlight the decline in voter support for Biden after the debate, others, including The New Yorker and The Associated Press, suggest that he should continue his campaign. Two opinion pieces in The New York Times and an article in The Atlanta Journal Constitution advocate for Biden to withdraw from the race, citing concerns about his age and debate performance, respectively. Despite this, both Al Jazeera English and NBC News report that Biden's family encourages him to remain in the race, while an opinion piece in The New York Times acknowledges Biden's positive qualities but ultimately concludes that he should step down due to his age.
